The police&#8217;s Kay Makhubele says a second illegal miner remains trapped in another mine shaft in the area. JOHANNESBURG The search and rescue operation for an illegal miner trapped in a disused Johannesburg mine has been halted due to the poor weather conditionsOn Thursday, the body of another illegal miner was found at the surface of an illegal mine near the old Highgate shopping center.The police s Kay Makhubele says a second illegal miner remains trapped in another mine shaft in the area at the corner of commando and main reef roadsHe says it s not yet clear when the rescue operation will resume. I m not sure when as when they were starting with the operation the rain then started and the search was called off because the place is dangerous. 